Pipelines de Detection Engineering for the SIEM's 

 Creation of rule:

	- Create the logic of the rule in SIGMA / XML
	- Upload it to the Gitlab repo in Staging directory
		- (AUTOMATED) Rule uploaded to BOTH SIEM's
		- (AUTOMATED) Entry into the Backoffice in testing
		- (AUTOMATED) Create a reminder in a week to check results from the rule
		- (AUTOMATED) Create an entry in the drape table with the results
	- Final check from the DE Analyst
		- IF the rule is good for prod
			- Upload to the production folder
			- (AUTOMATED) Update the backoffice entry to be in the prod queue
		- ELSE the rule needs changes
			- Make the changes to the rule
			- (AUTOMATED) New rule is uploaded
			- (AUTOMATED) New reminder for the next week
			- (AUTOMATED) Update the stats on the drape table
	- Redo the evaluation

---

 Updates of rules:
	
	- Evaluate the change needed
	- Create the rule with the same format
		- Upload to the staging directory
		- (AUTOMATED) RE upload on both siems (Removal of the old, in with the new)
		- (AUTOMATED) Set into the testing queue in backoffice
	- Evaluation of the results after 3 days
		- (AUTOMATED) Update the stats on the drape table
		- Review of the results
	- Upload into the prod directory
		- (AUTOMATED) Update in both SIEMs'
		- (AUTOMATED) Update the queue in backoffice